  "prompt": "What is the best gift a student can give to teacher in graduation?",
  "response": "Choosing a meaningful and heartfelt gift for a teacher at graduation can show your appreciation for their guidance and support. Here are some thoughtful ideas:\n\n1. **Personalized Thank-You Note**: A heartfelt, handwritten letter expressing your gratitude and how they\u2019ve impacted your life is one of the most meaningful gifts.\n\n2. **Customized Keepsake**: A personalized item like a mug, plaque, or engraved pen with a heartfelt message or a quote.\n\n3. **Gift Card**: A gift card to their favorite caf\u00e9, bookstore, or store allows them to treat themselves.\n\n4. **Plant or Flowers**: A small potted plant or bouquet symbolizes growth and appreciation, and it\u2019s a lasting reminder of your gratitude.\n\n5. **Books**: A book they\u2019d enjoy, either related to their subject or a personal interest, with a handwritten note inside.\n\n6. **Personalized Artwork**: A custom drawing, painting, or print that reflects their influence or something they love.\n\n7. **Class Gift**: Collaborate with classmates to give a larger, meaningful gift, like a framed class photo or a donation in their name.\n\n8. **Practical Items**: Something useful for their classroom or personal life, like a high-quality notebook, organizer, or stationery.\n\n9. **Memorable Experience**: Tickets to a concert, theater performance, or a relaxing day at a spa.\n\n10. **Donation in Their Name**: Donate to a cause or charity they care about in their honor.\n\nThe best gift is one that reflects their personality, your relationship, and your gratitude. Even a simple, heartfelt token can mean the world to a teacher who has made a difference in your life.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
